$interpreted: Insect POW: Princess! You've come back to save us!
Tindoiimu: Shh, don't call attention to the guards.
Tindoiimu: Just hold on, I'll get you out of here.
Insect POW: You've broken the locks! Amazing!
Tindoiimu: Quick, come out.
Izumi: Good evening, Princess. The moon is lovely tonight~
Izumi: I see you're back to set them free.
Tindoiimu: You... You knew I'd come back to save them?
Izumi: Isn't that just common sense?
Izumi: Beyata truly wished you wouldn't, of course.
Beyata: ...It will only bring sadness...
Beyata: I don't want you to be sad, Princess.
Izumi: Listen, if these prisoners of war are freed,
Izumi: The Alliance will levy sanctions, and the demihumans will starve!
Izumi: Please, Princess, just go back to the guesthouse and have fun with your friends. Get some sleep. Wouldn't that be better for everyone?
Tindoiimu: Have fun? ...I've been a hostage since I was nine years old.
Tindoiimu: I've never had any fun! No one in the Insect Tribe has!
Nigel: —Enough! Both of you!
Izumi: Nigel!?
Izumi: Ayaaa~ The gang's all here!
Izumi: What's wrong, Nigel?
Izumi: Don't tell me you're recruiting members of the Insect Tribe for your cause now?
Nigel: ...The Insect Tribe and the demihumans really aren't so different. I've come to understand their plight.
Nigel: How could I see their oppression and turn a blind eye? I'd be no different from those tyrants in The Kingdom of the Sun.
Izumi: Ah...
Tindoiimu: Sorry, but... who are you?
Nigel: My name is Nigel, from Atlas. I'm leader of the demihumans.
Nigel: I'd like to help you and the rest of the Insect Tribe.
Tindoiimu: Atlas...? Wasn't it destroyed forty years ago?
Nigel: And so it was. I've traveled far to come here to bolster the ranks of the demihumans and finally rebuild Atlas.
Tindoiimu: ...Rebuild...
Nigel: That's right. Atlas may be gone, but we still live on, and this is not over. Far from it.
Tindoiimu: ......
Nigel: I've heard about your past, and how your tribe is treated.
Nigel: I used to be full of hatred, I wanted nothing but revenge. I was quite the extremist.
Tindoiimu: ...But now you're not?
Nigel: Now I understand what it means to be a leader.
Nigel: There's something more important than revenge and dignity...
Nigel: It's being a becon for the downtrodden, the unwanted... and helping them find a way to live on!
Tindoiimu: ......
Nigel: I know it will be hard for you to abandon revenge.
Nigel: But you must, no matter how much it takes.
Nigel: Otherwise, you'll never be a leader.
Tindoiimu: But... The Insect Tribe and the Alliance will never reach an agreement!
Nigel: ...Well, if you've nowhere to go in the east,
Nigel: then come to Atlas. You're welcome there.
Tindoiimu: —You mean... abandon our home? Everything we've ever known?
Nigel: For your tribe, I think first finding a way to survive would be most important. What happens after that can be dealt with when it comes.
Tindoiimu: ...Thank you.
Tindoiimu: I will... think about what you've said.
Nigel: Great!
Izumi: Ayaa~ Sorry to cut in here, but...
Izumi: Even if we were to let the princess go with these hostages, she'd never make it out of Hot Spring Street.
Tindoiimu: What...?
Beyata: Everyone sold to work on Hot Spring Street is restricted from leaving. There are guards at every exit.
Beyata: If you want to bring these hostages out, well...
Beyata: I'm afraid it'll be impossible. You might as well change your mind, princess. I don't want to see you cry...
Nigel: Hmm... Let me think...
Nigel: Oh yeah, Baa-Baa!
Izumi: Oh right, her!
Nigel: She's a merchant, she could probably get around the guards!
Nigel: Let's get her over here...
Tindoiimu: Wait, a merchant?
Nigel: Yes, her name is Baa-Baa. Do you know her?
Tindoiimu: Baa-Baa...? You don't mean—
Baa Baa: Heya~ Bit late to be callin' me over here, but I'm here!
Baa Baa: I'm tired as, though...
Tindoiimu: Baa-Baa, it really is you!
Baa Baa: Ah! Princess!
Baa Baa: It's been ages! You look alright, though. I was worried about ya!
Tindoiimu: Baa-Baa... I'm glad you're okay.
Tindoiimu: I've been worried about you ever since we split up back at those qilin trials.
Baa Baa: I got swept away somewhere and wandered around for ages... Had to keep checking my dad's old map til' I finally found the way out.
Baa Baa: Swear I almost scared myself to death, thought I was done for! But, you know, winners never quit, quitters never win!
Nigel: So, you both know each other? Well that will make this easy, then!
Nigel: It seems you can already trust Baa-Baa, is that right, princess?
Tindoiimu: ...She's saved my life once already, so yes.
Baa Baa: Eh? What are you two on about?
Nigel: Baa-Baa, we have a mission... a job, that only you can do.
Hestia: So booorrinngg...
Puggi: Super boringgg!!!
Hestia: I mean, I'm thankful for Maeok getting us out of our cell and into this room, since Sennosuke's been dealt with...
Hestia: Really, that was super nice of her... but...
Puggi: But I'm getting serious cabin fever staying cooped up in here all day!!!!
Puggi: And it's all Pang's fault! That traitor--!!!
Puggi: He abandoned us and ran off to Hot Spring Street!
Hestia: Yeah! We've been in the east for so long already, and I haven't even seen my own tribe!
Hestia: I've heard a lot of mermaids have been sold off to work at Hot Spring Street, so I wanna go there too! Stupid Pang!
Puggi: Yeah, he's so selfish!!
Puggi: He said he'd help Hesty find her tribe, and then what does he do!? He runs off to that super cushy-soft-fragrant Hot Spring Street!
Puggi: And everyone knows Hot Spring Street's filled with the most babe-licious babes in the east!!
Puggi: Eh... Uh oh, I didn't mean to say that...
Hestia: ......
Puggi: He-Hesty, did you... hear what I just said?
Hestia: ......
Puggi: Don't get the wrong idea! I really want to help you find your people! I just thought, If we're gonna go there anyway, then I could...
Hestia: Hmph! You're just as bad as Pang! Some friends you are!! I'm done talking to both of you!!!
Puggi: Nooo, Hesty!!! Don't be maddd~~
Hestia: What was that sound?
Puggi: It's the beating of my heart, Hesty~ Because I'm thinking about you~
Hestia: This isn't the time for jokes, Puggi! Just get out of the way!
Hestia: Listen, it's footsteps... A lot of footsteps! But it's the middle of the night, the Alliance guards should all be off duty...
Alliance Guard: Izumi... can we trust...?
Alliance Guard: ...We've got to report... arbiter... quickly!!
Puggi: ...Seems like something happened? They're calling the arbiter?
Puggi: But the arbiter should be fast asleep by now...
Hestia: Something must be really wrong... I wonder if Pang's okay...
